&nbsp;
In addition, Asia is heating faster than the global average >, with temperatures last year almost two degrees Celsius higher than the average from 1961 to 1990. "The results of the report reflect," said OMM number one. "Many countries in the region have lived the hottest year ever recorded in 2023, accompanied by a series of extreme conditions, from drought and hot waves to floods and storms," the report states. The report on the state of Asia 2023 highlights the accelerated pace of the main indicators of climate change, such as surface temperature, glacier retreat and rising sea level, stating that they would have serious impacts on the societies, economies and ecosystems of the region.
&nbsp;
