&nbsp;
The Asian region of high mountain, centered on the Tibetan plateau, contains the largest volume of ice outside the polar regions. In recent decades, most of these glaciers have retired, and this has happened at an accelerated pace, according to OMM data: 20 of the 22 monitored glaciers in the region showed continuous mass loss last year. The report also states that the sea surface temperatures in the Northwest Pacific Ocean in 2023 were the highest ever recorded. Last year, 79 disasters were reported in Asia associated with hydrological risks. Of these, more than 80% were floods and storms, which caused more than 2,000 deaths. Nine million people were directly affected. "The floods were by far the main cause of death among the events reported in 2023", emphasizes the OMM, detecting the persistent high level of vulnerability of Asia to natural risk events.
&nbsp;
Following a typhoon, Hong Kong recorded 158.1 millimeters of rainfall in an hour on September 7, 2023, a record since the recordings began in 1884. The OMM states that it is urgent that national weather services in the region produce data to better alert risks. "It is essential that our actions and strategies reflect the urgency of this moment," says Saul. "Reducing greenhouse gas emissions and adapting to climate change is a fundamental necessity." &nbsp;

