&nbsp;
The Foreign Minister of Ankara, Hakan Fidan, anticipated that 20 protocols of understanding will be signed. Erdogan, after Baghdad, will go to Erbil, the capital of Iraqi Kurdistan, autonomous but not independent. For the Turkish leader the priority &nbsp; remains the fight to the Pkk, led by the Turks with repeated operations and air raids beyond the border, which in recent years have strengthened the relations with the Iraqi Kurdistan, dominated by the Barzani clan, but at the same time they have brought up the tension with the central government of Baghdad.
&nbsp;
In mid-March a Turkish delegation, led by the head of secret services and the Foreign Minister, went to the Iraqi capital. Turkey is determined to create a 30 km deep bearing area across the border, the Iraqi government has announced that the Pkk will be included in the list of terrorist organizations. The Iraqi Foreign Minister, Fuad Hussein, confirmed that the two countries work on a road map "to overcome differences on the Pkk".
&nbsp;
