&nbsp;
In addition to the highway, a high-speed line, with freight trains and passengers capable of travelling up to 300 kilometers per hour, but also the establishment of commercial sorting centers, industrial complexes and the possibility of integrating the project with an pipeline and possibly a pipeline. A total investment estimated at 17 billion dollars, which according to the forecasts should yield 4 billion dollars a year and create at least 100 thousand jobs. It is a project on which Erdogan strongly points, in contrast to the plan of Israel and the United Arab Emirates to connect India, the Middle East and Europe through the economic corridor Imec.
&nbsp;
Another hot topic and the center of controversy in recent years is that of water resources. The two countries, if they really want to collaborate in the near future, are forced to seek a solution that satisfies both in the management of the water of Tigri and Euphrates and its tributaries. The two rivers that give name to the Mesopotamia region are born in Turkey, but constitute vital resources for the Iraqi economy, put at risk by the numerous dams built by the Turkish government over the past 20 years and climate change.
